summaries.short: Season Two Premiere. After settling a score with the baseball exec who screwed him, Kenny Powers heads to Mexico to start a new life.
summaries.full: Season Two Premiere. After settling a score with the baseball exec who screwed him out of a big-league comeback, Kenny Powers heads to Mexico to start a new, more anonymous life. Befriended by a neighboring Mexican family and a sultry bar singer named Vida, Kenny decides to make a baseball comeback with a hapless local team, the Chaross.

summaries.short: Charros owner Sebastian Cisneros agrees to throw out all the stops in promoting Kenny Powers' return to organized baseball.
summaries.full: Charros owner Sebastian Cisneros agrees to throw out all the stops in promoting Kenny Powers' return to organized baseball, but Kenny loses motivation after learning a secret about April from an old friend.

summaries.short: In the Season One finale, Kenny says goodbye to his life as a schoolteacher after scoring a big-league job offer.
summaries.full: In the Season One finale, Kenny says goodbye to his life as a schoolteacher--and bids farewell to Dustin and his family--after he's tendered a big-league job offer in Tampa.

summaries.short: Kenny resorts to form on the diamond, and scores points with Vida.
summaries.full: Puzzled by the Mexican fans' lukewarm reception, Kenny starts a grassroots PR campaign to burnish his image. But it takes a vintage Powers flare-up to bring the fans to their feet. Kenny makes inroads with Vida by inviting her to Sebastian's yacht party.

summaries.short: Kenny decides to give up his comeback, but his resolve is tested by a car dealer and his new pet celebrity.
summaries.full: Convinced he's lost his stuff, Kenny decides to give up his comeback dreams and move on as a working stiff--but his resolve is tested by arrogant car dealer Ashley Schaeffer and his new pet celebrity, a major-league arch-nemesis named Reg Mackworthy.
